net.hudup.core.alg.cf

Class MemoryBasedCF

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.alg.AbstractAlg
      • net.hudup.core.alg.Recommender
        • net.hudup.core.alg.MemoryBasedRecommender
          • net.hudup.core.alg.cf.MemoryBasedCF
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Alg
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NeighborCF

    @CFAnnotation
public abstract class MemoryBasedCF
extends MemoryBasedRecommender
    Note, the abstract class Recommender represents all recommendation algorithm. Two typical inherited classes of Recommender are MemoryBasedRecomender and ModelBasedRecommender which in turn are abstract classes for memory-based recommendation algorithm and model-based recommendation algorithm. There are two common trends: content-base filtering (CBF) and collaborative filtering (CF) in building up a recommendation algorithms as follows:
    • The CBF recommends an item to user if such item has similarities in contents to other items that he like most in the past (his rating for such item is high). Note that each item has contents which are its properties and so all items will compose a matrix, called item content matrix
    • The CF, on the other hand, recommends an item to user if his neighbors which are other users similar to him are interested in such item. User’s rating on any item expresses his interest on that item. All ratings on items will also compose a matrix, called rating matrix.
    Both CBF and CF have their own strong and weak points.
    This abstract class represents the memory-based recommendation algorithm with collaborative filtering (CF), called memory-based CF recommender. Memory-based CF recommender uses rating matrix (as a part of the internal dataset dataset) stored in memory for filtering task in recommendation. As mentioned, two main methods of any recommender are estimate(...) and recommend(...). This class only defines method recommend(...) so that classes that extend it must defines the other one estimate(...).

      • recommend

        public RatingVector recommend(RecommendParam param,
                              int maxRecommend)
        Description copied from class: Recommender
        This method is the most important one in recommendation task. Any class that extends this abstract class must implement this method. Note that the role of user and the role of item are exchangeable. Rating vector can be user rating vector or item rating vector. Please see RatingVector for more details. The input parameters are a recommendation parameter and the maximum recommended items (users) in the returned rating vector. The output result is a list of recommended items (users) which is provided to the user (item).
        Specified by:
        recommend in class Recommender
        Parameters:
        param - recommendation parameter. Please see RecommendParam for more details of this parameter.
        maxRecommend - the maximum recommended items (users) in the returned rating vector.
        Returns:
        list of recommended items (users) which is provided to the user (item), represented by RatingVector class. The number of items (users) of such list is specified by the the maximum number.
